# crawl-gui-domains.txt — default Start URLs for crawl-gui.hta
#
# Rename this file to "crawl-gui-domains.txt" (drop the .example) and keep it
# next to crawl-gui.hta. When the GUI opens, every non-comment line below becomes
# a Start-URL row — so you can preload as many sites as you want. They're crawled
# sequentially with the same settings.
#
# Rules:
#   - one URL per line
#   - blank lines and lines starting with #  are ignored
#   - an inline " # comment" after a URL is trimmed (a #fragment in the URL is kept)
#
# Uncomment / replace the examples below with your own sites:
#
# https://example.com/
# https://docs.example.com/
# https://blog.example.com/   # quarterly check
